# Backend, Data, Auth & Billing

## Database (Drizzle + Neon)

- Schema lives in `packages/database/src/schema.ts`; access via `getDb()` from
  `@video-lib/database`. Always guard with `isDatabaseConfigured()` first.
- Use `db.select()/insert()/update()` with `eq()` from `drizzle-orm`. Use inferred types
  (`User`, `Export`, `CatalogTemplate`) instead of hand-written shapes.
- Schema changes ship via `npm run db:push` (drizzle-kit), not raw SQL migrations.

## Auth (Clerk)

- Server code resolves the user through helpers in `lib/auth/user.ts`:
  `getCurrentDbUser()` (nullable), `requireDbUser()`, `requireAdminUser()`.
- `getOrCreateUser` lazily provisions a DB row on first sign-in (20 starter credits).
- Route protection is centralized in `middleware.ts` via `createRouteMatcher`. When adding
  protected routes, update the matcher there rather than checking auth ad hoc.
- Admins are configured by `ADMIN_USER_IDS` (comma-separated) — never hardcode IDs.

## API route conventions

```ts
export async function GET() {
  try {
    const user = await getCurrentDbUser();
    if (!user) return NextResponse.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, { status: 401 });
    // ...
  } catch (error) {
    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : "Failed.";
    return NextResponse.json({ error: message }, { status: 500 });
  }
}
```

- Return `NextResponse.json`. Use 401 unauthorized, 403 forbidden, 500 with the error message.
- Gate plan/credit features with helpers (`hasProAccess`, `canExportResolution`,
  `canExportProTemplate`), never inline plan-string comparisons in routes.
- Stripe webhooks (`api/webhooks/stripe`) and Clerk webhooks are public routes; verify
  signatures and keep them out of the protected matcher.
